## Two-Machine Battery Script

The script below is intended to run on the central machine. It starts `node_central` locally and starts `sensor_node` remotely through SSH on the sensor machine.

```bash
SENSOR_HOST=user@192.168.0.20 ./scripts/run_two_machine_battery.sh
```

Default battery:

* Warmup from 2 to 20 sensors, one run per sensor count
* Deletes `benchmarks` after warmup
* Test phase from 2 to 100 sensors
* 10 repetitions for each sensor count
* Fixed payload: 20 KB
* Fixed rate: 100 Hz
* One central node and one sensor node

Both Docker containers must be running with host networking:

```bash
docker run -it \
  --name ros2_humble \
  --net=host \
  -v "/path/to/ros2_ws:/root/ros2_ws" \
  osrf/ros:humble-desktop
```

Useful overrides:

```bash
SENSOR_HOST=user@192.168.0.20 \
CENTRAL_CONTAINER=ros2_humble \
SENSOR_CONTAINER=ros2_humble \
ROS_DOMAIN_ID=42 \
BENCHMARK_DURATION_SEC=180 \
./scripts/run_two_machine_battery.sh
```

Logs are saved on the central machine in:

```text
battery_logs/
```


export ROS_DOMAIN_ID=31


net.core.rmem_max=2147483647
